page.title: 18A WEEK'S NEWS WEST READING
page.content: 10th June 1985 {1/}Trial witness on contract killer list.{2/}palace deny owing money to Reading firm.{3/}Guard knifed in wages snatch.{4/}School shocked by cannabis smoking.{5/}64 year old man marries after 31 years {other stories {6/ }Digging was started on Elgar road relief by resident Association chairperson Helen Thomas and councillor Joe Williams. {7/}experienced Nurse has quit Reading hospital because of low staffing. {8/}South Oxfordshire planning chief opposes third Reading bridge.{9/} Animal rights demonstration at circus show{10/}Katesgrove area pilots reading's first neighbourhood watch scheme.
